uk.ac.cam.cl.groupproject12.lima.hbase

Class Threat

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.cam.cl.groupproject12.lima.hadoop.AutoWritable
      • uk.ac.cam.cl.groupproject12.lima.hbase.Threat
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable

    public class Threat
extends AutoWritable
    A Class used to represent a single row in the HBase Threat table.
    The threat was processed at timeProcessed (in UNIX time) in the logged data for the router identified by routerId. The threat consists of flowCount different flows, the earliest starting at startTime, the latest ending at endTime. flowDataTotal gives the total number of bytes carried by all of the flows considered as part of this attack.
    If the threat targets a single IP it will be stored in destIP; if the threat originates from a single IP it will be stored in srcIP.

        packetCount - The number of packets sent in this threat.
        flowDataTotal - The total amount of data to be transferred during this threat.
